div1.p: In the District Court of the third Judicial District of Washington Territory of Washington holding thems at Seattle for the Countries of King & Kitsap:
In the matter of the application of C. W. Hutchinson on for Habeas Corpus}
Territory of Washington County of King ss. Order No 4704

An now it appearing to me by petition of C. W. Hutchinson that he is illegally restrained of his liberty by one Lewis VanW H Harris Doren in this county of King without proper authority - now this is to order that the said Lewis Van DorenW H Harris do appear before me as the District Court house of King County in Seattle, where I am holden open the day of November AD 1885 at 2 1/2 O'Clock P.M. and then and there to have and produce the body of the said C. W. Hutchinson that I may inquire of and determine why
the said Hutchingson is so illegally restrained and the Clerk of the said District Court is ordered to issue a writ in accordance with this order,
Given this 12th day of November AD 1885
In the Dist. Ct. of the 3rd Judicial Dist of Washington Territory
In re petition of C W Hutchinson for Habeas Corpus
FILED NOV 12 1885 James Seavey Clerk. By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk
